



Council Chamber, November 8, 1775.



Sir: Agreeable to your request, signified to the Board by your Excellencys Aid-de-Camp, Mr. Harrison, we have caused Mr. Smithwick to be apprehended, and herewith send him to wait your Excellencys order, under custody of the Sergeants guard who brought Mr. Cox here this morning.1

In the name and by order of the Council:
James Otis, President

